{"session_id":"svc-1778399811534325124","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-10T07:56:53.558903321Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-b194d20f-20260510T075644-6854a3cf","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260510T075644-6854a3cf/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260510T075644-6854a3cf/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260510T075644-6854a3cf/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260510T075644-6854a3cf/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260510T075644-6854a3cf/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Decomposition depth cap\u0026#xA;This bead is already at decomposition depth 2. Do not create another child layer; if it is still too large, reject the split with a short explanation and write no_changes_rationale.txt instead.\u0026#xA;\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-b194d20f\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eRename DDx execution internals away from agent vocabulary\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;DDx internals still use `cli/internal/agent`, AgentRunRuntime, AgentRunner, ExecuteBead*, and related names for DDx-owned task execution. After the spec update, those names will be wrong: DDx owns task execution, while Fizeau owns routing/execution internals. Keeping `agent` as the DDx package name invites future routing-policy drift and confusion with real external AI agents.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;cli/internal/agent/ contains DDx-owned queue drain, bead attempt, review, worktree, session evidence, and Fizeau adapter code. Existing refactor bead ddx-387a0178 still targets cli/internal/agent/try and cli/internal/agent/work and acceptance #7 keeps deprecated `ddx agent` aliases. Existing terminology bead ddx-3ee4ddcf still says not to remove legacy aliases. Those plans conflict with the no-deprecation decision and with FEAT-010 task-execution vocabulary.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;After specs are ratified and the Fizeau contract cleanup release is integrated, split/rename DDx-owned internals to names matching responsibilities, for example `cli/internal/taskexec`, `cli/internal/taskexec/run`, `cli/internal/taskexec/try`, `cli/internal/taskexec/work`, `cli/internal/fizeauadapter`, and `cli/internal/runlog` or equivalent repo-consistent names. Rename exported/internal identifiers accordingly: AgentRunRuntime -\u0026gt; TaskRunRuntime or FizeauRunRuntime as appropriate; AgentRunner -\u0026gt; TaskExecutor/FizeauExecutor; ExecuteBead* -\u0026gt; Try/Attempt/Work terms. Keep `agent` only in literal external-agent concepts, historical event keys that cannot be migrated safely, or third-party standards names.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;Do not remove the public `ddx agent` CLI in this bead unless it is already covered by ddx-d8474e0e. Do not change queue behavior, retry policy, review gates, or routing semantics. Do not implement Fizeau fuzzy matching. Do not rename durable tracker keys unless a migration plan is included in a separate bead.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PARENT AND DEPENDENCIES\u0026#xA;Parent: ddx-f088a3fd. Depends on: ddx-424fdac4 and ddx-7065edd1.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. DDx-owned production code no longer lives under `cli/internal/agent`; remaining `agent` package/path references are audited as literal external-agent, generated historical data, or compatibility storage.\u0026#xA;2. FEAT-010 package/path references match the implemented package names.\u0026#xA;3. All new or renamed DDx task-execution identifiers use run/try/work/taskexec/fizeauadapter vocabulary rather than Agent/ExecuteBead/ExecuteLoop vocabulary, except audited durable compatibility names.\u0026#xA;4. Existing stale beads ddx-387a0178 and ddx-3ee4ddcf are updated, closed as superseded, or otherwise made non-dispatchable so they no longer instruct workers to preserve `ddx agent` aliases or create new `cli/internal/agent` packages.\u0026#xA;5. `rg -n \u0026#34;cli/internal/agent|AgentRunRuntime|AgentRunner|ExecuteBead|ExecuteLoop|ddx agent\u0026#34; cli docs .agents/skills .claude/skills skills` returns only audited retained hits documented in the implementation notes.\u0026#xA;6. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... ./internal/... -run \u0026#34;Test.*(Run|Try|Work|Fizeau|Terminology|Routing).*\u0026#34; -count=1` passes after updating exact final test names.\u0026#xA;7. `cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./...` passes.\u0026#xA;8. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:execution, area:refactor, area:fizeau, kind:breaking\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-f088a3fd\" spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"8368edbc4543d9361d3f75bbf0d0ecd62af2f17d\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260510T075644-6854a3cf\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-010\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md\"\u003eFeature: Task Execution\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260510T075644-6854a3cf","base_rev":"8368edbc4543d9361d3f75bbf0d0ecd62af2f17d","bead_id":"ddx-b194d20f","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260510T075644-6854a3cf","correlation_id":"ddx-b194d20f:20260510T075644-6854a3cf","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260510T075644-6854a3cf/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"d5809b1429447497200adfb1f84c412615fd37f401d0e25b226072e15a6abb24","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-76441677","worker_id":""}}}
